Jordan Waddingham found the world's largest European wasp nest at Karoola in Tasmania . 
  The 12-year-old followed a trail of wasps after his mother offered him $20 to find the nest . 
  The 90-kilogram nest is measured at one metre tall and has a circumference of three metres . 
  It is the largest subterranean European wasP nest ever discovered . 
  The nest is on display at the Queen Victoria Museum and Art Gallery in Launceston . 
 